ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The totals for Canada for 2003 so far are 8255 birds submitted for
testing, 7595 birds tested, and 283 confirmed West Nile virus-positive. In
addition there were 2249 sightings of dead birds recorded. This represents
an increase of 862 birds tested and 77 more birds confirmed positive since
the last update on Thu 31 Jul 2003. There have been no extensions of range.
2 more equine cases have been confirmed in Alberta, and the number of
positive mosquito pools has increased by 2 (Ontario 1, Alberta 1).
A West Nile virus-positive blood donation has been reported in
Saskatchewan, and an imported human case is suspected in Ontario. The press
report in part [1] indicates that subsequently a non-imported case of human
West Nile virus infection has been confirmed in Ontario. - Mod.CP]
